ith their family. Very readable and beautifully illustrated, this book provides an extensive discussion of the people of Oaxaca, their way of life and their beliefs, which make the Day of the Dead logical and easily comprehensible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAll Souls' DayzMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aAll Souls' DayzMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aAltarszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aAltarszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aCemeterieszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aDeathxSymbolic aspectszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aDeathxSymbolic aspectszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 0aFasts and feastszMexicozOaxaca de Juárez. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aFukuda, Curt, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178238608740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782386087423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782386087/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK